casebody.data:
VENEY v. WARDEN OF MARYLAND PENITENTIARY [App. No. 34,

September Term, 1963.]

Decided December 12, 1963.

Before Henderson, Hammond, Horney, Marbury and Sybert, JJ.

Per Curiam.

For the reasons stated in his opinion filed in the lower court, Judge Sodaro properly dismissed without a hearing the second petition of Robert Veney for post conviction relief. The applica*613tion for leave to appeal from the order of dismissal will therefore be denied.

Application denied.
